{"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"topicSections":[{"title":"Trackers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/JTrackers\/documentation\/JTrackers\/ByteTracker","doc:\/\/JTrackers\/documentation\/JTrackers\/BoostTracker","doc:\/\/JTrackers\/documentation\/JTrackers\/OCSort"],"anchor":"Trackers"},{"title":"Data Types","identifiers":["doc:\/\/JTrackers\/documentation\/JTrackers\/TrackedObject","doc:\/\/JTrackers\/documentation\/JTrackers\/JamTrackError"],"anchor":"Data-Types"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/jtrackers\/jtrackers"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/JTrackers\/documentation\/JTrackers\/JTrackers"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Multi-object tracking algorithms for Swift, powered by a Rust engine."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"JTrackers provides Swift bindings for high-performance multi-object tracking","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"algorithms implemented in Rust. Each tracker takes per-frame detections and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"assigns persistent track identifiers across frames.","type":"text"}]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Supported-Algorithms","type":"heading","text":"Supported Algorithms"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/JTrackers\/documentation\/JTrackers\/ByteTracker"},{"type":"text","text":" — ByteTrack: two-stage matching using high and low-confidence detections."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/JTrackers\/documentation\/JTrackers\/BoostTracker"},{"type":"text","text":" — BoostTrack: IoU + Mahalanobis distance + shape similarity with optional BoostTrack+\/++ modes."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","ident